### THE DIVISIONS OF THE DAY.

It was in this way that they formerly computed time, and the divisions
of day: they enumerated eight parts of the day, and three hours in each
part, and reckoned thus, namely, the first hour, or the second, or the
third hour of midnight, dawn, vapourlessness, &c., and so in respect of
every one of the eight divisions.

